The HA titer of the inﬂuenza virus solution was determined
to be 64 for all samples at 0 h, immediately after the
application of virus suspensions onto the surface of each
material. At 1, 8, and 24 h post-virus application, the HA
titer on the surface of all samples was 32, demonstrating that
the HA titer of the inﬂuenza virus remained stable over time
without any marked decrease, irrespective of the material.
